message:
I'll comment on the code as I go through it:  
The following piece:  
-----------------------------  
.Do(_ =>  
 {  
 // Update UI each time we get a new search request.  
 this.listViewResults.Items.Clear();  
 this.labelStatus.Text = "Searching...";  
 });  
---------------------  
Has a drawback: This piece of code will run for each subscription. In your case you subscribe once, but it's a bad habit.  
You should either change it to a subscription, or use Publish() and .Connect() to capture the side-effects only once.
